    <p class="text-sm/6 sm:text-base/7">
      <strong>Expediate aims to make logging food simple</strong>. Athletes
      provide a comma-separated list of the food they ate, and the system parses
      it and provides a <strong
        ><a href="https://tr3.run/articles/diet-quality-score-dqs-explained"
          >Diet Quality Score (DQS)</a
        ></strong
      >.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm/6 sm:text-base/7">
      The goal of this project was to deliver a <strong
        >MVP wherein athletes could log data in a simple way and receive a basic
        DQS-informed summary</strong
      >. While features such as user accounts, detailed breakdowns and
      integration with other scoring systems would be useful, these were
      out-of-scope for the MVP.
    </p>

