    </h2>
    <p class="text-sm/6 sm:text-base/7">
      <strong>Diet Quality Score (DQS)</strong> is a rule-of-thumb system introduced
      by <a
        href="https://www.triathlete.com/nutrition/do-you-know-your-diet-quality-score-2/"
        target="_blank">Matt Fitzgerald</a
      > to help athletes measure diet quality without tracking every calorie.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm/6 sm:text-base/7">
      Fitzgerald&apos;s DQS is point-based and depends on two factors:
    </p>
